===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In bronze inscriptions, {{Han compound|ls=psc|府|勹|c1=p|c2=s|t2=person bending over|nocap=yes}}. In the modern script {{zh-l|*勹}} has changed to {{zh-l|*亻}}.

===Etymology===
Compare perhaps {{cog|my|ဖူး|t=to behold with reverence}}.<ref>{{R:sit:Luce 1981|page=33|head=-U Finals (48. to Behold with reverence or love))}}</ref>

